timeline
    title AOL4Free: The Arms Race (June–September 1995)
    section v1–v3 (Detectable)
        Jun 12 — Beta 1 : K1(free) sent after EVERY token
                         : Including after Dd (signon)
                         : Server logs CMis errors
        Jun 21 — Beta 2 : Fixed IM button bug
        Jul 1 — Beta 3  : Changed free area invocation
        Jul 1 — Beta 4  : Fixed screen name creation
        Jul 10 — Final 2.5 : First stable release
        Aug 4 — v1 (2.6) : Ported to AOL 2.6
                          : Extended to all tokens
        Aug 8 — v2       : Fixed IM billing hole
        Aug 26 — v3      : New free token
                          : Added mailbomber
    section AOL Detection
        Aug 31 : David Lippke discovers CMis bug
               : "filter the log for CMis"
               : K1 arrives before Dd completes
               : Session ID mismatch logged
    section v4 (Stealth)
        Sep 13 — v4 : Token table at 0x589A checks Dd
                    : CMPI.W #$4464, 1(A4) → BEQ skip
                    : Also skips Dg, LO, xG, vx
                    : Two dispatch tokens &colon; K1 + Kg
                    : Deferred injection via flags
                    : "totally Stealth"
